Title: Relates to granting on-premise alcohol retailers an extension of one year to renew their expired liquor license without any late fees during the COVID-19 state disaster emergency
Summary: Grants on-premise alcohol retailers an extension of one year to renew their expired liquor license without any late fees when such renewal date occurred during the COVID-19 state disaster emergency through the end of the 2020 year.
ActClause: AN ACT in relation to granting on-premise alcohol retailers an extension of one year to renew their expired liquor license without any late fees during the COVID-19 state disaster emergency
